post_text:
Kindergarten painted lions a few weeks ago & then we used cardboard to create a relief sculpture like the Maine artist Bernard Langlais. We haven’t finished by glueing the cut cardboard shapes into place yet. If you have some recycled cardboard boxes-students could make a new idea using this technique.
Please post a photo of your creation.

shared_text:
Bugs Are People Too the Art of Fran Gianfriddo
March 18 at 8:02 PM ·

FREE COLORING PAGES
A friend of mine, had the idea to share some of his art, so people with kids could print them out as coloring pages. I thought his idea was a good one, (so I'm copying him). Hopefully these images from my "Bugs Are People Too" series can hep keep little hands and minds busy during this prolonged "time out".
Copy and paste to a document file.
FEEL FREE TO SHARE!
See the entire collection of bugs at:
Etsy.com/shop/frangianfriddo
